      <akn:section eId="sec_32_1331_06">
        <akn:num>32-1331.06</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Hearings.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1331_06_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1331_06_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>If the Mayor, after investigation but before a hearing, has cause to believe that a person is violating any provision of this subchapter and the violation has caused, or may cause, immediate and irreparable harm to the public, the Mayor may issue a stop work order requiring the alleged violator to immediately cease and desist construction-related business activities. The order shall be served by certified mail or delivery in person.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1331_06_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_32-1331_06_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Any party aggrieved by a final order of the Mayor under subsection (c)(3) of this section may seek judicial review and appeal under ยง 2-510.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
